#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:1
msgid "Closures and Generics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:3
msgid ""
"Rust's zero-cost abstractions -- generics, closures, and trait bounds -- "
"work on the GPU. This is one of cuda-oxide's most distinctive capabilities: "
"you can write a single generic kernel that operates on any numeric type, or "
"pass a closure from the host to customize GPU behavior, all without runtime "
"overhead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:8
msgid "Generic kernels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:10
msgid ""
"A kernel can be generic over types, const values, and trait bounds, just "
"like any Rust function. The compiler monomorphizes each specialization into "
"a separate PTX entry point:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:14
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, thread, DisjointSlice};\n"
"use core::ops::Mul;\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn scale<T: Copy + Mul<Output = T>>(\n"
"    factor: T,\n"
"    input: &[T],\n"
"    mut out: DisjointSlice<T>,\n"
") {\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    let i = idx.get();\n"
"    if let Some(out_elem) = out.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        *out_elem = input[i] * factor;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:32
msgid "PTX naming"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:34
msgid ""
"Each monomorphization produces a distinct PTX entry point. Non-generic "
"kernels keep their plain function name. Generic kernels (including closure-"
"generic kernels) get a `_TID_<hex32>` suffix where `<hex32>` is rustc's "
"stable type-id hash of the concrete generated kernel function item, rendered "
"as 32 lowercase hex characters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "Instantiation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "PTX entry point name"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`vecadd` (non-generic)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`vecadd`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`scale::<f32>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`scale_TID_<hex32>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`scale::<MyType>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`tile::<4>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`tile_TID_<hex32>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`tile::<8>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`map::<f32, _>` (closure)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:0
msgid "`map_TID_<hex32>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:49
msgid ""
"Both the host launcher and the device backend ask the pinned rustc toolchain "
"for the same `FnDef` hash within one unified build, so the strings match "
"byte-for-byte. The function item contains its definition plus every ordered "
"type and const argument. The on-wire name therefore remains fixed-length "
"regardless of generic arity. Borrow lifetimes are erased before hashing, so "
"they do not create duplicate GPU code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:56
msgid ""
"Treat the suffix as a build artifact, not a permanent ABI: host code and PTX "
"must be built together with cuda-oxide's pinned rustc toolchain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:59
msgid "Launching generic kernels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:61
msgid ""
"When launching, specify the type parameter on the generated typed method. "
"That forces the concrete instantiation and lets the loader look up the "
"matching PTX entry point:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:65
msgid ""
"use cuda_core::LaunchConfig;\n"
"\n"
"// SAFETY: config is 1D and both buffers cover every launched index.\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    module.scale::<f32>(\n"
"        &stream,\n"
"        LaunchConfig::for_num_elems(N as u32),\n"
"        2.0f32,\n"
"        &input_dev,\n"
"        &mut output_dev,\n"
"    )\n"
"}\n"
".expect(\"Launch failed\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:81
msgid ""
"The generated method forces monomorphization of `scale::<f32>` so the "
"instantiation appears in the compiled PTX even though it is never called "
"directly on the CPU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:85
msgid "Const-generic kernels"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:87
msgid "Const parameters work on kernel and device-function entry points:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:89
msgid ""
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn add_value<const VALUE: u32>(mut output: DisjointSlice<u32>) {\n"
"    let index = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    if let Some(element) = output.get_mut(index) {\n"
"        *element += VALUE;\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:99
msgid ""
"add_value::<4> -> add_value_TID_<hash A>\n"
"add_value::<8> -> add_value_TID_<hash B>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:104
msgid "Use ordinary Rust turbofish syntax on the generated launch method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:106
msgid ""
"// SAFETY: config matches the kernels' 1D indexing and output bounds.\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    module.add_value::<4>(&stream, config, &mut output)?;\n"
"    module.add_value::<{ Config::VALUE }>(&stream, config, &mut output)?;\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:114
msgid ""
"The older `#[kernel(f32, i32)]` convenience form only supports one type "
"parameter. For const or mixed generics, use bare `#[kernel]` and specialize "
"at the launch site."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:118
msgid "Host closures as kernel arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:120
msgid ""
"cuda-oxide supports passing closures from the host to the GPU. This enables "
"powerful `map`-style patterns where the kernel's behavior is parameterized "
"by a function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:124
msgid ""
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn map<F: Fn(i32) -> i32>(f: F, input: &[i32], mut out: "
"DisjointSlice<i32>) {\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    let i = idx.get();\n"
"    if let Some(out_elem) = out.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        *out_elem = f(input[i]);\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:135
msgid "Launch with a closure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:137
msgid ""
"let factor = 3i32;\n"
"// SAFETY: config is 1D and both buffers cover every launched index.\n"
"unsafe {\n"
"    module.map::<_>(&stream, config, move |x| x * factor, &input_dev, &mut "
"output_dev)\n"
"}\n"
".expect(\"Launch failed\");\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:146
msgid "How closure arguments travel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:148
msgid ""
"The closure passes through the launch as one value -- not as a list of "
"captured fields. The launcher pushes a single driver argument (the whole "
"closure struct, captures and all), and the kernel receives it as one byval `."
"param`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:153
msgid ""
"host          factor = 3i32; cl = move |x| x * factor\n"
"              push one driver arg ─► closure struct { factor: i32 }\n"
"\n"
"GPU kernel    .entry map_TID_<hex>(\n"
"                .param .align 4 .b8 f[4],    ; one byval closure\n"
"                .param .u64 input_ptr,        ; slice still (ptr, len)\n"
"                .param .u64 input_len,\n"
"                ...\n"
"              )\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:165
msgid ""
"Slices keep their `(ptr, len)` flattening because that shape is shared by "
"the host launch helpers and the PTX entry-point layout. Only aggregate- by-"
"value parameters (closures and user structs passed by value) land as one "
"byval at the kernel boundary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:170
msgid ""
"A closure with no captures is a zero-sized type -- the backend drops the `."
"param` entirely, and the host launcher knows to skip it so the packet stays "
"aligned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:174
msgid "PTX naming for closures"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/closures-and-generics.md:176
msgid ""
"A closure-generic kernel gets the same `_TID_<hex32>` suffix as any other "
"generic kernel. The closure's anonymous type is part of the concrete "
"function item, so two distinct closure literals -- even ones with the same "
"`Fn` signature -- produce two distinct entry points:"
msgstr ""

